				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>yeah, but a significant proportion of the ipv6-using-v4-announces will probably be using teredo or 6to4. And as far as i know the checking would only involve a few bit operations, so it shouldn't be too hard.<br /><br />I agree that a tracker listening on a v6 interface is preferable, but just updating the software to do a few checks is far more realistic than convincing the hoster to run v6 for you.</p>
