<div id="p143" class="blockpost roweven">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#35&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=143#p143">2008-03-30 05:37:59</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=89618">The 8472</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Azureus Developer</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: Discussion of BEP 7: IPv6 Tracker Extension</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>@Olaf, agreed<br /><br />checks for an v4-announced ipv6 address<ul style="list-style-type: disc"><br /><li>that falls into the 2002::/16 block, which is 6to4: The ipv4 address must make up the following 4 bytes of the address, i.e. 128.128.128.128 could claim any v6 ip in the 2002:8080:8080::/48 block. To prevent flooding a tracker should only accept a limited amount of clients per /48 block and torrent.</li><br /><li>that falls into the 2001:0000::/32 block, which is teredo: the ipv4 address must make up the last 4 bytes of the v6 address, but inverted. i.e. 128.128.128.128 would map to 2001:0000:*:7F7F:7F7F<br />* means that various bit patterns may occur, as opposed to ::</li><br /><li>that falls into the ::ffff:0:0/96&nbsp; block, which is a v4-mapped v6 address: this simply announces ipv4-connectivity and must be treated as if the peer announces a v4 address explicitly. 128.128.128.128 would map to ::ffff:8080:8080 or ::ffff:128.128.128.128</li><br /><li>that falls into any other valid ipv6 unicast range: this should be treated similar to an ipv4 client announcing an unrelated ipv4 address, i.e. it is up to the tracker policy if such an address should be accepted, validated or discarded.</li><br /></ul><br /><br />Since there are various rules for parsing v6 addresses, including the special v4-mapped syntax and the omission of zeros it should be left to the library of the used language, if available.</p>
					<p class="postedit"><em>Last edited by The 8472 (2008-03-30 14:38:57)</em></p>
				</div>
				<div class="postsignature"><hr />Az dev</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
			<div class="postfootleft"><p>Offline</p></div>
			<div class="postfootright"><div>&nbsp;</div></div>
